16/12/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Parliament supported on Wednesday (December 15th) the abolishment of mandatory military service, effective on January 1st. 
As of then, military service will be only for those who volunteer to join, including women. 
The decision aims to professionalise the army, bringing it in line with international standards. 
(Tanjug, Beta, B92 - 15/12/10)
